  <abstract>Jeff Montgomery, USMC, wrote this letter to his future wife Ruth Hopper in Jackson, Tennessee. Montgomery is in training at the Marine Corps Barracks on Parris Island. He enlisted only a few weeks before the armistice. He discusses playing checkers with pals at the YMCA, cleaning his rifle, eating candy, and writing to his "beloved." He also mentions that they will begin shooting on the range the next day. "When seveny men shoot ten times in a minute there is some racket, but we get use to that."</abstract>
